Well, today I was flying this very plane.
First complaint: We need cute flight logbooks. Black is too boring, and pink is not really pink, it's more like salmon red.
I've wanted to fly since I was a child.
Today my dream came true... I flew a plane today. I'm still in shock.
flightaware data.
I plan to try again this Saturday. The weather doesn't look very good now, but today is only Monday.
It seems that the challenges in this area have already begun to emerge. Due to the FAA's stance on certain medications, I may find it difficult to obtain a medical certificate.
It's not impossible, but it will take a lot of time and involve a great deal of extra work.
Although this is a bit frustrating, it's just another problem that needs to be solved, and it seems "definitely" solvable at the moment. It just requires a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I will face next:
FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you're taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get a medical certificate.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If I ever have the chance to customize an airplane's tail number, it must be some variant of N1337_, where _ represents any available letter character.
Of course, the sun will rise as usual when I'm not around, haha. That's really disappointing.
I have to fly again. But this lousy weather is really not helping.
Welcome to the world of general aviation! 😜
Based on the ads YouTube thinks I should see, the videos it recommends to me, and the comments, I feel like the airlines tend to be conservative in their tracking.
If the weather permits, I'll fly again on Saturday.
Also, I found a pink flight log.
Good morning Saturday. I did this today ^_^
#TeaganAir
The flight log has officially been activated. I have 2.3 hours of flight time already ^_^
#TeaganAir
If you let me describe what it feels like to fly a small plane, I would say it's like driving a combination of a motorcycle/ATV and a boat at 4000 feet in the air.
On the ground, the situation changes rapidly. There is a certain level of instability on the ground, so a motorcycle/ATV is needed.
By the way, you might not know that when driving an airplane on the ground, you use your feet to control the direction, not the control stick. You use the rudder pedals and brakes. It's not a car.
When flying in the air, you will feel turbulence and shaking, similar to riding a ship on water. Although you can control the airplane, sometimes air currents can make you a bit disoriented, so you need to get used to flying in the air, just like sailors get used to sailing.
Regarding this, there is also a random fun fact:
Flying is very physically demanding. My back and legs are really sore today, feeling like I've been to the gym.
This is nothing like going for a drive on Sunday. In my novice opinion, it's more like a sport rather than cruising.
Dear friends, happy Saturday. Welcome to 4000 feet in the air.
Tomorrow I will fly again, and we will practice stalls and slow flight.
Today's weather was a bit unstable, but super fun. We practiced slow flight and stalls. Our ground speed once dropped to 16 miles per hour, while the airspeed was still at 65 miles per hour.
Today the weather was clear, though a bit hazy at high altitude, but the view was still great.
